# Create the subplots
n_cols = 7
n_rows = 6
fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=n_rows, ncols=n_cols)
fig.set_size_inches(20, 10)
for i in range(42):
    data = subject_time[subject_time["subject#"] == i+1]
    sns.regplot(x = data["test_time"], y = data["motor_UPDRS"],
                ax=axes[i//n_cols,i%n_cols], scatter_kws={"color": "blue"}, line_kws={"color": "yellow"})
    sns.regplot(x = data["test_time"], y = data["total_UPDRS"].rename("UPDRS"),
                ax=axes[i//n_cols,i%n_cols], scatter_kws={"color": "green"}, line_kws={"color": "yellow"})
plt.tight_layout()

from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error
from sklearn.metrics import r2_score
from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error
 
def printPredictions(y_true,y_pred, count):
  print(f"Predictions: ")
  print(y_true.assign(
      motor_UPDRS_pred = y_pred[:,0],
      total_UPDRS_pred = y_pred[:,1]   
  ).head(count).to_markdown(index = False))
 
def showResults(y_true, y_pred, count = 5):
  print("R2 score: ",r2_score(y_true,y_pred))
  print("Mean squared error: ",mean_squared_error(y_true,y_pred))
  print("Mean absolute error: ",mean_absolute_error(y_true,y_pred))
  printPredictions(y_true,y_pred, count)
In [32]:
import numpy as np
def mxize(array):
    n = array.size
    mx = np.ones((len(df), n))
    for i in range(n):
        mx[:, i] = array[i]
    return mx
    
def stdize(data):
    mean = np.mean(data, axis=0)    # 均值
    std_dev = np.std(data, axis=0)    # 标准差
    norm_data = (data - mxize(mean)) / mxize(std_dev)    
    return norm_data

def stdize_1(data):
    mean = np.mean(data)    # 均值
    std_dev = np.std(data)    # 标准差
    norm_data = (data - mean) / std_dev
    return norm_data

df2 = df.copy();
df2.iloc[:,3:-2] = stdize(df2.iloc[:,3:-2])
df2.iloc[:,1] = stdize_1(df2.iloc[:,1])
